attributes.title: JAPANESE POKEMON CENTER WITH CRIKEN AND REINA
attributes.caption: Welcome back to the Malort Era!
attributes.description: Welcome back to Behind the Cow Chop! This week Brett jet sets off to Japan and meets up with Criken and Reina Scully. They end up visiting the Japanese Pokemon Center. How fun! Also we have some old footage from this dumb go kart we bought and Criken shows up again at the warehouse to revive the Malort Era. For some reason?
attributes.display_title: JAPANESE POKEMON CENTER WITH CRIKEN AND REINA

attributes.title: OPENING A HAUNTED MYSTERY BOX FROM EBAY
attributes.caption: CAN YOU SEE SOMETHING?
attributes.description: Welcome back to Behind the Cow Chop! Today we've got quite a special treat for you. Aleks has been doing some online shopping and found a "mystery box" full of haunted goodies. What's inside? Will it curse us? How could it possibly get any worse? Let's watch and find out.
attributes.display_title: OPENING A HAUNTED MYSTERY BOX FROM EBAY

attributes.title: GONE SHOOTIN'
attributes.caption: WE'RE BERRY BOYS. THIS IS BERRY LAND
attributes.description: Welcome back to Behind the Cow Chop! This week we managed to make it out of Los Angeles, and head up to the great north west of California... or just like...  an hour away. But lucky for us we got gun expert Wyatt to help us out and shoot up all these random objects. Like Lindsey's 16 year old guitar. That's older than you! Wow!

attributes.title: UNBOXING A BLESSED/CURSED VOODOO DOLL
attributes.caption: LIVE LADY BUGS
attributes.description:
Welcome back to Behind the Cow Chop! Time to open up some of these packages that've been piling up. The items include: 

300 live lady bugs
boys with plants
sun chips
a fun dangerous weapon
aleks' voodoo doll

also let's not talk about what happens in the bathroom.

attributes.title: TWO BOYS SHARING A MALIBU HOTEL
attributes.caption: I DON'T LIKE THAT SHE'S A JUMPER
attributes.description: Welcome back to Behind the Cow Chop! This week the boys went over to Malibu for a mini getaway. But really... nothing happened. So.. let's check in on the bugs, and also buy a new mini fridge.
attributes.display_title: TWO BOYS SHARING A MALIBU HOTEL

attributes.title: OPENING HISSING COCKROACHES FROM THE MAIL
attributes.caption: YO YOU CAN'T MAIL US LIVE ANIMALS DUDE

attributes.display_title: OPENING HISSING COCKROACHES FROM THE MAIL

attributes.title: REBUILDING THE NOTRE DAME
attributes.caption: PUZZLE NOT CHALLENGE
attributes.description:
Welcome back to Behind the Cow Chop! This week Aleks has picked up a fun new vinyl player and we're going to add it to the basement set to spice things up. Aleks and Brett also try to build a miniature metal Notre Dame, but really- Aleks should have just picked up a PUZZ 3D.

Remember those bugs someone sent us? Brett went and gave them an extreme home makeover. Check out our bug update.

attributes.title: LOW KEY LIQUIDATION
attributes.caption: BUY OUR SHIT IDIOTS
attributes.description: Welcome back to Behind the Cow Chop! Let's take a look into the preparations for our huge Patreon Yard Sale. We got rid of a lot of junk! Also the premiere of the first ever "Beef Corner with John"

attributes.title: THE CALM BEFORE & AFTER THE SPICE GAUNTLET
attributes.caption: THAT'S A LOT OF VOMIT TO CLEAN UP!!
attributes.description: Holy crap that spice gauntlet was something else!  I don't even want to know how they went about cleaning that place up afterward.  But I'm sure you do, so enjoy even more vomit while watching this BTCC.
attributes.display_title: THE CALM BEFORE & AFTER THE SPICE GAUNTLET

attributes.title: 25 ROACH BABIES
attributes.caption: YOU'RE LIKE... THE ROACH GUY NOW
attributes.description: Well over the past week we've discovered Mama Roach had babies. Loads of babies. Matt and Garret are aiming to ollie the couch, so we'll see how that goes. And there's something living/rotting in our dishwasher.

attributes.title: ANOTHER SKATE CHOP INJURY
attributes.caption: I WISH I GOT HURT
attributes.description: Well we didn't really think we'd be here again. More injuries here at Skate Chop. Just to update you we'll be at RTX in a few days for a panel, a signing and a Patreon meet up! Check out our Patreon for more info on that! Also these fucking bug babies are huge wtf.

attributes.title: PLANTING NEW CROPS
attributes.caption: BE THE FIRST MAN ON PLANET SODA POP
attributes.description: It's variety hour here at Cow Chop, we've got a little bit of everything for ya. Fan mail, gardening, cool blanket sweatshirts, dancing, and russian snacks.

attributes.title: COUNTING OUR BABY ROACHES
attributes.caption: WHY ARE THERE DIFFERENT SIZES??
attributes.description: Yeah so those bugs had babies and we decided to count them finally and turns out there are over 50 so we're probably all gonna die now.

attributes.title: COW CHOP TRIES SURSTRÖMMING
attributes.caption: HOT BOY SUMMER
attributes.description: Ohhhh baby, it's a hot boy summer now. The boys are getting wet and wild as they make a mess and wash each other off. Someone sent us this surstromming so we're gonna try it and it's actually.....

attributes.title: OUTDOOR SHOWERS & CENTURY EGGS
attributes.caption: IT JUST KIND OF TASTE LIKE AN EGG
attributes.description:
What do you get when you mix a bunch of dirty bois with 100 years worth of fermentation. Whatever happened this week. We bought a new bug zapper to help reduce some of these lil flybois around the warehouse, and we got a bit distracted eating some century eggs.

Aleks also ended up investing in a new outdoor shower to help clean up after shoots... since apparently the boys showering together is a new recurring theme.

attributes.title: LAUNDRY DAY WITH THE BOYS
attributes.caption: SOMEONE GOT AWAY WITH SHITTING ON MY UNDERWEAR
attributes.description: Aleks purchased some new machinery for the warehouse. Time to teach all the boys how to do their own laundry. Some are better than others.

attributes.title: EATING THE WORLD'S SMELLIEST FRUIT
attributes.caption: CREAMY AND BUTTERY, JUST LIKE OUR LITTLE GARRETT
attributes.description: Thanks (NOT) Callum for sending us this smelly ass fruit. It's still in our fridge, spoiling the rest of our foods. Also you guys got any hot tips for breaking out of handcuffs?

attributes.title: HAPPY BIRTHDAY ALEKS
attributes.caption: IT FEELS SO GOOD TO BE OLD
attributes.description: Thanks for all these Denny's gifts. Happy Birthday Aleks

attributes.title: MUSICAL LIGHT BULB PRANK
attributes.caption: IT'S A LIGHTBULB THAT PLAYS MUSIC
attributes.description: This week on behind the Cow Chop, Matt & Garrett head to Home Depot to pick up...... well actually I don't recall because they got so distracted by this dang light bulb and 9.5 ft pirate ship, that who knows what they were picking up. Inevitably the light bulb that plays music does lead to Jakob's self destruction.

attributes.title: FINAL MERCH RELEASE & AREA 51 PREP
attributes.caption: WE WRECK THINGS, WE WRECK OUR OWN BUSINESS
attributes.description: Here's our final merch drop of 2019 and likely ever. Check it out, you can get the tarot card now and very soon be able to pick up the other pieces on the Rooster Teeth merch store. Also be sure to tune in tomorrow to see what happens with all these Area 51 gear we picked up. Thanks for watching. Bye
